Studio Project is a practical course during which musical pieces are recorded in the studio, selection is made from the recorded material, the musical piece is edited and mixed. The student is the sound engineer, sound director, arranging artist and producer of the project to be recorded.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Develop the students' skills, on the basis of their prior theoretical knowledge, to record groups performing a variety of music styles in the recording studio. Teach the student to communicate with musician or actor as producer. Give the practical skills for recording demanding projects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student having passed Studio Project:
knows recording studio working operations, can use recording studio equipment,
has a practical skills to do recording process in studio incl. preproduction, recording, postproduction, mixing, studio communication.
